How do you specify parametric types of parametric types? I.e. I'm trying to do this:
```abstract type Element{T} end

struct Line{T} &lt;: Element{T}
  DOF::Vector{T} # the field stored quantity
end

typeofdof(::Type{&lt;:Element{T}}) where {T} = T

struct Field{&lt;:Element{T}} where {T}
  DOF::Vector{T}
end```
but can't extract the type `T` from the type `Element` , I tried following the Parametric type doc page, but it doesn't really seem cover this nested type scenario... and I can't for the life of me figure it out. I'd like to be able to do something like `a = Field{Line{Float64}}()` eventually.

